etsys8021xExtensionsMIB.name: etsys8021xExtensionsMIB

revisions.description: Modifications to limit the number of stations that statistics are gathered for.
The initial version of this MIB module.

etsys8021xExtensionsMIB.contactinfo: Postal: Enterasys Networks 50 Minuteman Rd. Andover, MA 01810-1008 USA Phone: +1 978 684 1000 E-mail: support@enterasys.com WWW: http://www.enterasys.com
etsys8021xExtensionsMIB.description: This MIB module defines a portion of the SNMP enterprise MIBs under Enterasys Networks' enterprise OID pertaining to IEEE 802.1X authentication. This MIB is designed to supplement and be used in connection with the standard IEEE 802.1X-2001 MIB. It provides a convenient way to retrieve authentication status for station- based access control. (Here, a MAC address is a much more natural table index than a port or interface number.)

etsysDot1xAuthStationTable.name: etsysDot1xAuthStationTable
etsysDot1xAuthStationTable.description: A table that contains basic status information for the Authenticator PAEs associated with station-based virtual ports.

etsysDot1xAuthStationEntry.name: etsysDot1xAuthStationEntry
etsysDot1xAuthStationEntry.description: Each conceptual row contains basic information about a station-based Authenticator PAE. The most natural label for such a PAE is the MAC address of the Supplicant that it manages, and that, in some sense, called the PAE into existence. So we index the table by the Supplicant MAC address.

etsysDot1xAuthStationAddress.name: etsysDot1xAuthStationAddress
etsysDot1xAuthStationAddress.description: The 48-bit IEEE media access control address of the Supplicant associated with the logical station-based access control port.

etsysDot1xAuthStationPaePort.name: etsysDot1xAuthStationPaePort
etsysDot1xAuthStationPaePort.description: The dot1xPaePortNumber of the shared-media port that is associated with this Authenticator PAE.

etsysDot1xAuthStationPaeState.name: etsysDot1xAuthStationPaeState
etsysDot1xAuthStationPaeState.description: The current value of the Authenticator PAE state machine.

etsysDot1xAuthStationBackendAuthState.name: etsysDot1xAuthStationBackendAuthState
etsysDot1xAuthStationBackendAuthState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

etsysDot1xAuthStationUserName.name: etsysDot1xAuthStationUserName
etsysDot1xAuthStationUserName.description: The User-Name representing the identity of the Supplicant PAE.

etsysDot1xAuthConfigTable.name: etsysDot1xAuthConfigTable
etsysDot1xAuthConfigTable.description: A table that contains configuration objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each station-based virtual port. Station-based configuration management poses several rather major inconveniences, including a large number of rows, rows indexed by MAC address (rather than by user), and rows that come and go. Port-level and Authentication-Server-based management are quite a bit more convenient. Thus, most of the objects in this table are read-only; a way to see how other settings have interacted if you need this information for troubleshooting purposes.

etsysDot1xAuthConfigEntry.name: etsysDot1xAuthConfigEntry
etsysDot1xAuthConfigEntry.description: Configuration information for a station-based Authenticator PAE.

etsysDot1xAuthInitialize.name: etsysDot1xAuthInitialize
etsysDot1xAuthInitialize.description: The initialization control for this Authenticator PAE. Setting this attribute to TRUE causes the PAE to be initialized. The attribute value reverts to FALSE once initialization has completed.

etsysDot1xAuthReauthenticate.name: etsysDot1xAuthReauthenticate
etsysDot1xAuthReauthenticate.description: The reauthentication control for this Authenticator PAE. Setting this attribute to TRUE causes the Authenticator PAE state machine to reauthenticate the Supplicant. Setting this attribute FALSE has no effect. This attribute always returns FALSE when it is read.

etsysDot1xAuthAdminControlledDirections.name: etsysDot1xAuthAdminControlledDirections
etsysDot1xAuthAdminControlledDirections.description: The current value of the administrative controlled directions parameter for the virtual port.

etsysDot1xAuthOperControlledDirections.name: etsysDot1xAuthOperControlledDirections
etsysDot1xAuthOperControlledDirections.description: The current value of the operational controlled directions parameter for the virtual port.

etsysDot1xAuthAuthControlledPortStatus.name: etsysDot1xAuthAuthControlledPortStatus
etsysDot1xAuthAuthControlledPortStatus.description: The current value of the controlled Port status parameter for the virtual port.

etsysDot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl.name: etsysDot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl
etsysDot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl.description: The current value of the controlled Port control parameter for the virtual port.

etsysDot1xAuthQuietPeriod.name: etsysDot1xAuthQuietPeriod
etsysDot1xAuthQuietPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the quietPeriod constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

etsysDot1xAuthTxPeriod.name: etsysDot1xAuthTxPeriod
etsysDot1xAuthTxPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the txPeriod constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

etsysDot1xAuthSuppTimeout.name: etsysDot1xAuthSuppTimeout
etsysDot1xAuthSuppTimeout.description: The value, in seconds, of the suppTimeout constant currently in use by the Backend Authentication state machine.

etsysDot1xAuthServerTimeout.name: etsysDot1xAuthServerTimeout
etsysDot1xAuthServerTimeout.description: The value, in seconds, of the serverTimeout constant currently in use by the Backend Authentication state machine.

etsysDot1xAuthMaxReq.name: etsysDot1xAuthMaxReq
etsysDot1xAuthMaxReq.description: The value of the maxReq constant currently in use by the Backend Authentication state machine.

etsysDot1xAuthReAuthPeriod.name: etsysDot1xAuthReAuthPeriod
etsysDot1xAuthReAuthPeriod.description: The value, in seconds, of the reAuthPeriod constant currently in use by the Reauthentication Timer state machine.

etsysDot1xAuthReAuthEnabled.name: etsysDot1xAuthReAuthEnabled
etsysDot1xAuthReAuthEnabled.description: The enable/disable control used by the Reauthentication Timer state machine (IEEE 802.1X-2001 Section 8.5.5.1).

etsysDot1xAuthKeyTxEnabled.name: etsysDot1xAuthKeyTxEnabled
etsysDot1xAuthKeyTxEnabled.description: The value of the keyTransmissionEnabled constant currently in use by the Authenticator PAE state machine.

etsysDot1xAuthStatsTable.name: etsysDot1xAuthStatsTable
etsysDot1xAuthStatsTable.description: A table that contains the statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each supplicant/station.

etsysDot1xAuthStatsEntry.name: etsysDot1xAuthStatsEntry
etsysDot1xAuthStatsEntry.description: The statistics information for an Authenticator PAE.

etsysDot1xAuthEapolFramesRx.name: etsysDot1xAuthEapolFramesRx
etsysDot1xAuthEapolFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAPOL frames of any type that have been received by this Authenticator.

etsysDot1xAuthEapolFramesTx.name: etsysDot1xAuthEapolFramesTx
etsysDot1xAuthEapolFramesTx.description: The number of EAPOL frames of any type that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

etsysDot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx.name: etsysDot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx
etsysDot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx.reference: IEEE 802.1X-2001 Section 9.4.2, EAPOL Start frames received
etsysDot1xAuthEapolStartFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Start frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

etsysDot1xAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx.name: etsysDot1xAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx
etsysDot1xAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx.reference: IEEE 802.1X-2001 Section 9.4.2, EAPOL Logoff frames received
etsysDot1xAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Logoff frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

etsysDot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.name: etsysDot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx
etsysDot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.reference: IEEE 802.1X-2001 Section 9.4.2, EAPOL Resp/Id frames received
etsysDot1xAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.description: The number of EAP Resp/Id frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

etsysDot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx.name: etsysDot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx
etsysDot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx.reference: IEEE 802.1X-2001 Section 9.4.2, EAPOL Response frames received
etsysDot1xAuthEapolRespFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAP Response frames (other than Resp/Id frames) that have been received by this Authenticator.

etsysDot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.name: etsysDot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx
etsysDot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.reference: IEEE 802.1X-2001 Section 9.4.2, EAPOL Req/Id frames transmitted
etsysDot1xAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Req/Id frames that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

etsysDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx.name: etsysDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx
etsysDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx.reference: IEEE 802.1X-2001 Section 9.4.2, EAPOL Request frames transmitted
etsysDot1xAuthEapolReqFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Request frames (other than Rq/Id frames) that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

etsysDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.name: etsysDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx
etsysDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.reference: IEEE 802.1X-2001 Section 9.4.2, Invalid EAPOL frames received
etsysDot1xAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the frame type is not recognized.

etsysDot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.name: etsysDot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx
etsysDot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.reference: IEEE 802.1X-2001 Section 9.4.2, EAP length error frames received
etsysDot1xAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the Packet Body Length field is invalid.

etsysDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameVersion.name: etsysDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameVersion

etsysDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameVersion.description: The protocol version number carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

etsysDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameSource.name: etsysDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameSource
etsysDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameSource.reference: IEEE 802.1x Section 9.4.2, Last EAPOL frame source
etsysDot1xAuthLastEapolFrameSource.description: The source MAC address carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

etsysDot1xAuthDiagTable.name: etsysDot1xAuthDiagTable
etsysDot1xAuthDiagTable.description: A table that contains the diagnostics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each Port. An entry appears in this table for each port that may authenticate access to itself.

etsysDot1xAuthDiagEntry.name: etsysDot1xAuthDiagEntry
etsysDot1xAuthDiagEntry.description: The diagnostics information for an Authenticator PAE.

etsysDot1xAuthEntersConnecting.name: etsysDot1xAuthEntersConnecting
etsysDot1xAuthEntersConnecting.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions to the CONNECTING state from any other state.

etsysDot1xAuthEapLogoffsWhileConnecting.name: etsysDot1xAuthEapLogoffsWhileConnecting
etsysDot1xAuthEapLogoffsWhileConnecting.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from CONNECTING to DISCONNECTED as a result of receiving an EAPOL-Logoff message.

etsysDot1xAuthEntersAuthenticating.name: etsysDot1xAuthEntersAuthenticating
etsysDot1xAuthEntersAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from CONNECTING to AUTHENTICATING, as a result of an EAP-Response/Identity message being received from the Supplicant.

etsysDot1xAuthAuthSuccessWhileAuthentica.name: etsysDot1xAuthAuthSuccessWhileAuthenticating
etsysDot1xAuthAuthSuccessWhileAuthentica.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to AUTHENTICATED, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating successful authentication of the Supplicant (authSuccess = TRUE).

etsysDot1xAuthAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthentic.name: etsysDot1xAuthAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthenticating
etsysDot1xAuthAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthentic.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating authentication timeout (authTimeout = TRUE).

etsysDot1xAuthAuthFailWhileAuthenticatin.name: etsysDot1xAuthAuthFailWhileAuthenticating
etsysDot1xAuthAuthFailWhileAuthenticatin.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to HELD, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating authentication failure (authFail = TRUE).

etsysDot1xAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthentica.name: etsysDot1xAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticating
etsysDot1xAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthentica.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of a reauthentication request (reAuthenticate = TRUE).

etsysDot1xAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenti.name: etsysDot1xAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticating
etsysDot1xAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenti.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message being received from the Supplicant.

etsysDot1xAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenti.name: etsysDot1xAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticating
etsysDot1xAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenti.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Logoff message being received from the Supplicant.

etsysDot1xAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthentica.name: etsysDot1xAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticated
etsysDot1xAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthentica.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of a reauthentication request (reAuthenticate = TRUE).

etsysDot1xAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenti.name: etsysDot1xAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticated
etsysDot1xAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenti.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message being received from the Supplicant.

etsysDot1xAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenti.name: etsysDot1xAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticated
etsysDot1xAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenti.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to DISCONNECTED, as a result of an EAPOL-Logoff message being received from the Supplicant.

etsysDot1xAuthBackendResponses.name: etsysDot1xAuthBackendResponses
etsysDot1xAuthBackendResponses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an initial Access-Request packet to the Authentication server (i.e., executes sendRespToServer on entry to the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authenticator attempted communication with the Authentication Server.

etsysDot1xAuthBackendAccessChallenges.name: etsysDot1xAuthBackendAccessChallenges
etsysDot1xAuthBackendAccessChallenges.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an initial Access-Challenge packet from the Authentication server (i.e., aReq becomes TRUE, causing exit from the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authentication Server has communication with the Authenticator.

etsysDot1xAuthBackendOtherRequestsToSupp.name: etsysDot1xAuthBackendOtherRequestsToSupplicant
etsysDot1xAuthBackendOtherRequestsToSupp.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an EAP-Request packet (other than an Identity, Notification, Failure or Success message) to the Supplicant (i.e., executes txReq on entry to the REQUEST state). Indicates that the Authenticator chose an EAP-method.

etsysDot1xAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFrom.name: etsysDot1xAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromSupplicant
etsysDot1xAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFrom.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives a response from the Supplicant to an initial EAP-Request, and the response is something other than EAP-NAK (i.e., rxResp becomes TRUE, causing the state machine to transition from REQUEST to RESPONSE, and the response is not an EAP-NAK). Indicates that the Supplicant can respond to the Authenticator's chosen EAP-method.

etsysDot1xAuthBackendAuthSuccesses.name: etsysDot1xAuthBackendAuthSuccesses
etsysDot1xAuthBackendAuthSuccesses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Success message from the Authentication Server (i.e., aSuccess becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to SUCCESS). Indicates that the Supplicant has successfully authenticated to the Authentication Server.

etsysDot1xAuthBackendAuthFails.name: etsysDot1xAuthBackendAuthFails
etsysDot1xAuthBackendAuthFails.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Failure message from the Authentication Server (i.e., aFail becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to FAIL). Indicates that the Supplicant has not authenticated to the Authentication Server.

etsysDot1xAuthSessionStatsTable.name: etsysDot1xAuthSessionStatsTable
etsysDot1xAuthSessionStatsTable.description: A table that contains the session statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each supplicant. An entry appears in this table for each supplicant.

etsysDot1xAuthSessionOctetsRx.name: etsysDot1xAuthSessionOctetsRx
etsysDot1xAuthSessionOctetsRx.description: The number of octets received in user data frames from the supplicant PAE during the session.

etsysDot1xAuthSessionOctetsTx.name: etsysDot1xAuthSessionOctetsTx
etsysDot1xAuthSessionOctetsTx.description: The number of octets transmitted in user data frames to the supplicant PAE during the session.

etsysDot1xAuthSessionFramesRx.name: etsysDot1xAuthSessionFramesRx
etsysDot1xAuthSessionFramesRx.description: The number of user data frames received from the supplicant PAE during the session.

etsysDot1xAuthSessionFramesTx.name: etsysDot1xAuthSessionFramesTx
etsysDot1xAuthSessionFramesTx.description: The number of user data frames transmitted to the supplicant PAE during the session.

etsysDot1xAuthSessionId.name: etsysDot1xAuthSessionId
etsysDot1xAuthSessionId.description: A unique identifier for the session, in the form of a printable ASCII string of at least three characters.

etsysDot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.name: etsysDot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod
etsysDot1xAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.description: The authentication method used to establish the session.

etsysDot1xAuthSessionTime.name: etsysDot1xAuthSessionTime
etsysDot1xAuthSessionTime.description: The duration of the session in seconds.

etsysDot1xAuthSessionTerminateCause.name: etsysDot1xAuthSessionTerminateCause
etsysDot1xAuthSessionTerminateCause.description: The reason for the session termination.

etsysDot1xAuthStatsSupported.name: etsysDot1xAuthStatsSupported
etsysDot1xAuthStatsSupported.description: Defines the objects supported in the Authenticator Statistics Table.

etsysDot1xAuthDiagSupported.name: etsysDot1xAuthDiagSupported
etsysDot1xAuthDiagSupported.description: Defines the objects supported in the Authenticator Diagnostics Table.

etsysDot1xAuthSessionSuppportedObjs.name: etsysDot1xAuthSessionSuppportedObjs
etsysDot1xAuthSessionSuppportedObjs.description: Defines the objects supported in the Authenticator Session Statistics Table.

etsysDot1xMaxCapableAuthStations.name: etsysDot1xMaxCapableAuthStations
etsysDot1xMaxCapableAuthStations.description: The maximum number of stations this device can authenticate.

etsysDot1xMaximumStationsStatsGathered.name: etsysDot1xMaximumStationsStatsGathered
etsysDot1xMaximumStationsStatsGathered.description: The maximum number of stations that this device can gather statistics, diagnostics, and session statistics for.

etsysDot1xCurrentStationsStatsGathered.name: etsysDot1xCurrentStationsStatsGathered
etsysDot1xCurrentStationsStatsGathered.description: The number of stations that this device is currently gathering statistics, diagnostics, and session statistics for.

etsysDot1xAuthStationWatchTable.name: etsysDot1xAuthStationWatchTable
etsysDot1xAuthStationWatchTable.description: A table containing the MAC addresses of stations that statistics, diagnostics, and session statistics will be kept for. This table's existence is due to the realization that devices may not have the resources to keep all of this data for all the authenticated stations; however, there is a need when debugging a network for these statistics. This compromise solution allows the network administrator to pick which stations to collect data for. If the maximum number of stations this device can collect data for is equal to the maximum number of stations the device can authenticate than this table has no effect or meaning. If the maximum number of stations this device can collect data for is 0 then this table has no effect or meaning. Please note: even though a station may be placed into the watch table, the statistics and diagnostic information that is acquired is ultimately determined by the device's capability to acquire that data. The statistics, diagnostics, and session statistics tables all have a read only object that allow the network administrator to determine what information the device can acquire.

etsysDot1xAuthStationWatchEntry.name: etsysDot1xAuthStationWatchEntry
etsysDot1xAuthStationWatchEntry.description: Each row contains the MAC address of a station that statistics, diagnostics, and session statistics will be kept for.

etsysDot1xAuthInfoStationAddress.name: etsysDot1xAuthInfoStationAddress
etsysDot1xAuthInfoStationAddress.description: The MAC address of a station that statistics, diagnostics, and session statistics will be kept for.

etsysDot1xAuthInfoStationRowStatus.name: etsysDot1xAuthInfoStationRowStatus
etsysDot1xAuthInfoStationRowStatus.description: A control that allows entries to be added, activated, deactivated, and removed from this table. When the value of this object is 'active' none of the other objects in this conceptual row can be modified. Setting this object to the 'active' state from the 'notInService' state will cause the collection of the above described statistics. Setting this object to any other valid state from the 'active' state will cause the collection of the above described statistics to stop. Setting this object to the 'active' state from the 'active' state will not have any affect. Conceptual rows that have been in the 'notInService' state for more than a device specific time period MAY be destroyed by the managed entity.

etsysDot1xAuthDiagGroup.name: etsysDot1xAuthDiagGroup

etsysDot1xAuthSessionControlGroup.name: etsysDot1xAuthSessionControlGroup
etsysDot1xAuthSessionControlGroup.description: A collection of objects providing statistics about the current or last sessions for Authenticator PAEs running on ports that use station-based access control.
